<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="kicker">What is agreed before departure</p>
    <h2>Not "as it happens on the road".</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Documents and crossing format</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>We need passenger passports and understanding of the trip purpose (tourism / business / personal). On that basis we send the exact list of what to carry and the format of the specific crossing.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Car on the other side</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>For most Brazil–Mercosur pairs we can continue with one car (with the right paperwork). On some routes a handover to a local car right after the crossing is faster and more economical. Decided ahead of time.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Timing and overnight stops</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>On long legs an overnight stop is built in at an agreed point (hotel, apartment — by your preference). It is not "stopping wherever we end up", it is part of the plan.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Fallback scenario</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>For border queues, road repairs, weather or rule changes — a plan B is agreed in advance: alternative crossing, extra overnight, schedule shift.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

